 EWC.CONNECTED‚Üêconnected
 ‚éïPW‚Üê1000

‚çù Grid InputMode demo. InputModeKey is specified like the Accelerator property ‚Äî
‚çù a (keyNumber shiftState) pair. Here we override the F2 default with
‚çù Ctrl+Shift+A = (65 3): 65 is the key number for "a", 3 = Shift(1)+Ctrl(2).
‚çù Scroll mode: cursor keys move between cells. Press Ctrl+Shift+A to switch to
‚çù InCell mode, where cursor keys move within the cell's text; press it again to
‚çù switch back.

 F‚Üê'F1'
 F eWC'Form' 'Grid InputMode (InputModeKey = Ctrl+Shift+A)'(50 50)(430 580)('Coord' 'Pixel')

 values‚Üê5 2‚ç¥‚ç¨
 values[1;]‚Üê'Apple' 150
 values[2;]‚Üê'Banana' 250
 values[3;]‚Üê'Cherry' 50
 values[4;]‚Üê'Date' 75
 values[5;]‚Üê'Fig' 100
 colTitles‚Üê'Product' 'Quantity'
 cellWidths‚Üê130 90

 ‚çù Size (height width): fit all 5 rows + col-title band and both columns
 ‚çù (TitleWidth 40 + 130 + 90 = 260 + border) with no scrollbar.
 (F,'.G')eWC'Grid'('Posn'(120 20))('Size'(120 280))('Values' values)('ColTitles' colTitles)('RowTitles'(‚ç≥5))('CellWidths' cellWidths)('TitleWidth' 40)('CurCell'(1 1))('VScroll' ¬Ø1)('InputMode' 'Scroll')('InputModeKey'(65 3))

‚çù Cell editors: text (Product) and numeric (Quantity).
 (F,'.G.E1')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.G.E2')eWC'Edit'('FieldType' 'Numeric')
 (F,'.G')eWS'Input'((F,'.G.E1')(F,'.G.E2'))
 cellTypes‚Üê5 2‚ç¥1 2
 (F,'.G')eWS'CellTypes' cellTypes

 ‚çù Posn y=52 keeps the text clear of the auto-added demo menu (top-right, ~y0-44).
 (F,'.Info')eWC'Label'('Caption' 'Scroll mode: arrow keys move between cells. Press Ctrl+Shift+A (the InputModeKey) to switch to InCell mode, where arrow keys move within the cell text. Press it again to switch back.')(52 20)(55 540)
